section.section:
In addition to adequate reserves required by § 5-103 of this title for outstanding losses, a title insurer shall maintain a statutory reserve or unearned premium reserve of at least an amount computed as follows:
8% of the total amount of the risk premiums written in the calendar year for title insurance contracts shall be as assigned originally to the reserves; and
during each of the 20 years that follow the year in which the contract is issued, the reserves applicable to the contract shall be reduced in accordance with the following formula:
35% of the aggregate sum on July 1 of the year next succeeding the year of addition;
15% of the aggregate sum on July 1 of each of the succeeding 2 years;
10% of the aggregate sum on July 1 of the succeeding year;
3% of the aggregate sum on July 1 of each of the succeeding 3 years;
2% of the aggregate sum on July 1 of each of the succeeding 3 years; and
1% of the aggregate sum on July 1 of each of the succeeding 10 years.
